OL,3,CEverything you need to know about the
OL,4,Cbizarre sport - Cornish Hurling
OL,6,F"It is unlikely now that a ball will
OL,7,Fbe hurled more than 6 or 7 times.
OL,8,FDepends on whether the person can
OL,9,Fafford to buy a new one.
OL,11,FJeremy Annear is an artist who owns a
OL,12,Fgallery opposite the starting point
OL,13,Ffor the game. He like many shop owners
OL,14,Fin the town always boards up his
OL,15,Fwindows to make sure no accidents
OL,16,Fhappen.
OL,18,F"All can go anywhere and it's a heavy
OL,19,Fsilverball, so it's much cheaper to
OL,20,Fput this up than to possibly run into
OL,21,Fpaying for a replacement glass."
