OL,3,CEverything you need to know about the
OL,4,Cbizarre sport - Cornish Hurling
OL,6,F"For someone who has never been here
OL,7,Fthey'd probably see it as quite rough
OL,8,Fbut it's not so bad when you've done a
OL,9,Ffew years of it and get stuck in."
OL,11,FThis year the players were encouraged
OL,12,Fto keep the ball in the town for the
OL,13,Ffirst hour of the game before making a
OL,14,Fdash for the winning goal.
OL,16,FIt is supposedly lucky to get a touch
OL,17,Fon the ball, so many spectators were
OL,18,Foffered a chance to pass it around
OL,19,Fbefore the competition hotted up.
